Package edu.cs2430.assignment3

Class ScheduleEntry

java.lang.Object
edu.cs2430.assignment3.ScheduleEntry
public final class ScheduleEntry extends Object
A class to store an entry for a schedule.
A schedule entry is a single course for a single semester. The entry is uniquely identified by the uuid.
A schedule entry can be constructed but not modified after construction. Therefore, there are no setter methods. The concept of a non-modifiable object is called immmutabe
Using the "final" keyword in front of the class definition prevents this class from being inherited from other classes.
